Class GnError

java.lang.Object
  com.gracenote.gnsdk.GnError
All Implemented Interfaces:
gnsdk_javaConstants
public class GnError
extends java.lang.Object
implements gnsdk_javaConstants

GNSDK error condition

Provides information about an error condition triggered within GNSDK including error code, API and module.

Helper methods are also provided to check if the error condition is a warning or an error, a result of a cancellation request or is equivalent to another error code.

GnError also provides access to GNSDK package identifiers and error codes. There is also a static helper method that compares two error codes allowing your application to correlate returned error codes with known error codes if required.

For example if you application wishes to perform specific behavior when an out of memory condition occurs you can, 

 
 // where error is a GnError instance received from GNSDK 
 if ( error.isError(GnError.GNSDKERR_NoMemory) ) { 
        // perform out of memory processes 
 }

Similarly you can compare error codes received from GNSDK via a GnException as, 

 
 try { 
        // some operation 
 } catch (GnException e) { 
        // where error is a GnError instance received from GNSDK 
        if ( GnError.isErrorEqual(e.errorCode(), GnError.GNSDKERR_NoMemory) ) { 
                // perform out of memory processes 
        } 
 }

isErrorEqual

public static boolean isErrorEqual(long error1,
                                   long error2)
Determine if two error codes are equal. Error code contain information beyond error condition, they also contain severity and package identifier. This method strips that information away and compares just the error condition. This is useful if your application needs to compare a returned error code with a known error code. Known error codes can be accessed via GnError object.

Returns:
True if the error conditions represented by the two error codes is equivalent
